-- Cotton Climbs 5.5% to Record in Zhengzhou as Shortage Attracts Investors
-- B y   L u z i   A n n   J a v i e r
-- 2010-11-08T01:25:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-08/cotton-climbs-5-5-to-record-in-zhengzhou-as-shortage-attracts-investors.html
Cotton futures advanced for a sixth
straight session in Zhengzhou, extending their record. The
contract for May delivery rose as much as 5.5 percent to 32,960
yuan ($4,952) a metric ton on the Zhengzhou Commodity Exchange,
before trading at 32,580 yuan at 9:25 a.m. local time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Poole at 
 jpoole4@bloomberg.net  